    • Method Detail

      • getMaxDoc

        public long getMaxDoc()
        Returns:
        the total number of documents. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getDocCount

        public long getDocCount()
        Returns:
        the number of documents that have at least one term for this field, or -1 if this measurement isn't available. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getDensity

        public int getDensity()
        Returns:
        The percentage of documents that have at least one value for this field. This is a derived statistic and is based on: 'doc_count / max_doc'

      • getSumDocFreq

        public long getSumDocFreq()
        Returns:
        the sum of each term's document frequency in this field, or -1 if this measurement isn't available. Document frequency is the number of documents containing a particular term. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getSumTotalTermFreq

        public long getSumTotalTermFreq()
        Returns:
        the sum of the term frequencies of all terms in this field across all documents, or -1 if this measurement isn't available. Term frequency is the total number of occurrences of a term in a particular document and field. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getMinValue

        public T getMinValue()
        Returns:
        the lowest value in the field. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getMaxValue

        public T getMaxValue()
        Returns:
        the highest value in the field. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getMinValueAsString

        public abstract java.lang.String getMinValueAsString()
        Returns:
        the lowest value in the field represented as a string. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.

      • getMaxValueAsString

        public abstract java.lang.String getMaxValueAsString()
        Returns:
        the highest value in the field represented as a string. Note that, documents marked as deleted that haven't yet been merged way aren't taken into account.
